<HEAD>Grandson Has Ice-Skating Accident</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS grafs 2-3 pvs beginning `The White ...' with 5 grafs to
UPDATE with number of stitches, president's stiff neck. Picks up 4th graf
pvs `She started ...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush gave a light-hearted account
Thursday of a ``catastrophic ice-skating accident'' in which his
13-year-old grandson ``bit the dust.''
   Young George P. Bush said later he had five stitches in his chin
after the accident at a public skating rink about two blocks from
the White House.
   The president also was ailing.
   ``I have a pain in the neck _ seriously,'' Bush told reporters
during an afternoon news conference.
   The president clearly had trouble moving his head, and White
House press secretary Marlin Fitzwater said Bush got a stiff neck
while lying on a couch Thursday morning reading an intelligence
report. Fitzwater said a doctor gave Bush some medication, which he
declined to identify.
