   Investors took the Panama crisis in stride with only a few brief
blips registering on financial markets around the world.
   The dollar, oil and many stocks moved higher Wednesday on the
news of the surprise U.S. military action, but prices later receded
amid the usual concerns about interest rates and the economy.
